Just click to order.

117
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:09,850
(Take this one for example.)

118
00:13:09,850 --> 00:13:11,370
(The Peach Blossom Luck Cat.)

119
00:13:11,370 --> 00:13:14,940
(That's right, you guessed it.
It brings romance and good fortune.)

120
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:17,180
(We've got five thousand total today.)

121
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:19,820
(Everyone, raise your lucky right hand,)

122
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:20,980
(give it a wave,)

123
00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:22,130
(and place your orders quickly!)

124
00:13:22,130 --> 00:13:23,890
(That's right, just like that.)

125
00:13:44,650 --> 00:13:45,770
Officer,

126
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:47,250
I already told you last time.

127
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,890
That woman drank a lot that night.

128
00:13:49,890 --> 00:13:51,770
Nothing else unusual happened.

129
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:55,730
Did any of you hand her water?

130
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:57,490
Or see her drinking any?

131
00:13:58,130 --> 00:14:01,460
We weren't in the room the whole time,

132
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,980
but we didn't give her water.

133
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:04,940
Manager Yang,

134
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,370
when we took your statement last time,

135
00:14:07,370 --> 00:14:10,100
I remember there were
three waiters present,

136
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,850
right?

137
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:11,610
Yes.

138
00:14:11,610 --> 00:14:13,340
Then why are there only two today?

139
00:14:13,340 --> 00:14:14,580
Where's the other one?

140
00:14:14,980 --> 00:14:16,220
She's resigned.

141
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:17,530
Resigned?

142
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:18,340
Yes.

143
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:19,420
When was that?

144
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:22,610
Shortly after that incident happened.

145
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:25,130
She said she found a better job.

146
00:14:25,980 --> 00:14:27,340
Do you know where she is now?

147
00:14:37,177 --> 00:14:39,460
Meili, these officers
would like a word with you.

148
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:40,770
I'm sorry,

149
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:42,340
we'll just need a bit of your time.

150
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:42,730
It's fine.

151
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:43,570
Please, have a seat.

152
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:44,980
We

153
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:47,010
went to your previous workplace.

154
00:14:47,010 --> 00:14:48,130
They said you'd changed jobs.

155
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:49,220
Why did you move here?

156
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:50,730
There's this lady.

157
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:52,580
She thought I was quite capable at work,

158
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:54,300
so she introduced me to this place.

159
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,890
The environment's better here,

160
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:57,100
and the pay's higher, too.

161
00:14:57,420 --> 00:14:58,610
Right, that's fair.

162
00:14:58,610 --> 00:14:59,610
Who's this lady?

163
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:00,820
Ms. Tao.

164
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,130
She was at that dinner, too.

165
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:05,850
Show her the photo.

166
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:08,690
Is this her?

167
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:11,850
Yes.

168
00:15:12,730 --> 00:15:13,580
Tao Jie, right?

169
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:16,010
Have you known her long?

170
00:15:16,460 --> 00:15:17,340
No.

171
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:19,730
Then why did she
recommend you for a job?

172
00:15:20,130 --> 00:15:22,220
She came by the shop
to chat with me one day.

173
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:23,890
She said we got along well.

174
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,730
Then we realized
we were from the same hometown,

175
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:27,220
so she helped me find this job.

176
00:15:27,220 --> 00:15:28,130
Same hometown, huh?

177
00:15:28,130 --> 00:15:28,770
Yes.

178
00:15:28,890 --> 00:15:30,100
Ah, hometown ties.

179
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,220
That explains it.

180
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,100
Where are you from?

181
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:33,940
Zhi County.

182
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:35,060
Zhi County.

183
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:37,340
You're here because

184
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,610
of that case, aren't you?

185
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:40,220
Let me ask you,

186
00:15:40,770 --> 00:15:43,100
the night Ms. Ye got drunk,

187
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:45,220
did anyone give her water?

188
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:46,980
Yes, I did.

189
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,420
What's wrong? Don't scare me.

190
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:03,420
It's fine. Relax.

191
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:04,530
Just tell us the truth.

192
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:09,060
Did you pour that glass
of water yourself?

193
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:10,660
No.

194
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:13,420
After Ms. Ye vomited that night,

195
00:16:13,420 --> 00:16:14,980
she looked really uncomfortable,

196
00:16:15,220 --> 00:16:17,100
and Mr. Fan
handed me a glass of water.

197
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:17,980
Waiter.

198
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:19,940
Yes, Sir?

199
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:21,220
Do me a favor.

200
00:16:22,010 --> 00:16:24,580
Take this glass of water
to my colleague.

201
00:16:24,580 --> 00:16:27,010
She's had a bit too much to drink.
The one in the coat.

202
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:28,580
It'll help her sober up.

203
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:29,420
Alright.

204
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:30,260
Thank you.

205
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,080
Water.

206
00:16:33,090 --> 00:16:34,580
Miss, would you like some water?

207
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,420
Have a drink.

208
00:16:42,111 --> 00:16:43,890
So it was Mr. Fan
who handed you the water?

209
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:47,090
Fan Jiancheng?

210
00:16:47,370 --> 00:16:48,210
Yes.

211
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:58,060
Captain Chen, in that drug case
you're investigating,

212
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:59,010
is there anyone from Nancheng

213
00:16:59,010 --> 00:17:01,088
on the list of registered buyers
of that medicine?

214
00:17:01,577 --> 00:17:03,190
Alright, let me know
if anything comes up.

215
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:04,250
Okay, thanks.

216
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,290
Check if Fan Jiancheng has any record

217
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:09,940
of purchasing controlled drugs.

218
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,020
Got it.

219
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:18,340
(Shop for Transfer)

220
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:31,460
Nan,

221
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:33,380
everything's ready.

222
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:37,090
You and your wife are really leaving?

223
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:38,380
Starting over somewhere new.

224
00:17:38,977 --> 00:17:40,733
You've canceled the memberships, right?

225
00:17:45,530 --> 00:17:47,010
I've found a few repair shops for you.

226
00:17:48,050 --> 00:17:49,250
They're all run by my friends.

227
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,660
The only thing is, they're a bit far.

228
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:53,810
It might be inconvenient
for your commute.

229
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:55,620
But the business is good,

230
00:17:55,620 --> 00:17:56,490
and the pay's higher.

231
00:17:57,090 --> 00:17:58,420
You can pick whichever you like.

232
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,380
Choose one that suits you.

233
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:03,660
I wanted to take over the shop,

234
00:18:03,660 --> 00:18:05,666
but I don't have enough money.

235
00:18:05,844 --> 00:18:07,490
I've scraped some together
from my family,

236
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:10,010
and borrowed from friends,
but it's still not enough.

237
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:10,850
How much short?

238
00:18:11,180 --> 00:18:12,020
Thirty thousand.

239
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,900
Nan, can you wait for me?

240
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,180
I'll borrow some more
when I go home for Chinese New Year.

241
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:18,290
No need.

242
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:19,422
Forget the thirty thousand.

243
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:20,530
That's not right.

244
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:22,220
You've been with me for so long.

245
00:18:23,155 --> 00:18:25,266
Do you think I'd care
about thirty thousand yuan?

246
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,530
All I want

247
00:18:30,530 --> 00:18:31,660
is for you to look after it.

248
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:35,180
It's my hard work over all these years.

249
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:38,940
Don't worry, Nan.

250
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:41,530
I don't even know what to say.

251
00:18:42,180 --> 00:18:42,940
You and your wife

252
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:44,620
- need money the most right now...
- Enough.

253
00:18:44,620 --> 00:18:46,090
If we're buddies, don't make a fuss.

254
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:49,060
Thanks, Nan.

255
00:18:50,044 --> 00:18:52,050
Then treat that thirty thousand
as your share.

256
00:19:00,660 --> 00:19:02,420
Let's leave on the first of next month.

257
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:04,810
That soon?

258
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:08,380
You don't want to go?

259
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:09,620
No.

260
00:19:09,755 --> 00:19:11,250
I'm just worried it'll be hard for you.

261
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,660
Maybe wait
until Mom recovers before leaving.

262
00:19:13,940 --> 00:19:15,380
Nianwen's still at home anyway.

263
00:19:15,690 --> 00:19:17,250
We can start packing bit by bit.

264
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:18,810
It's not that far.

265
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:19,940
We can come back often.

266
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:21,610
Alright.

267
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,530
Once we've settled down,

268
00:19:24,088 --> 00:19:25,380
we can bring Mom to stay with us.

269
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:33,250
I warmed you some milk.

270
00:19:33,530 --> 00:19:34,940
It'll help you sleep.

271
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,660
You haven't been resting well lately.

272
00:19:37,250 --> 00:19:38,090
Alright.

273
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,380
It's late. Wash up and get some sleep.

274
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:02,810
(Alright, here we go.)

275
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:05,900
(Welcome, everyone,
to Fan's livestream.)

276
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,220
(Thanks for joining us.)

277
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:08,980
(Raise your lucky left hand,)

278
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:11,010
(wave it, shake it.)

279
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:13,010
(Wave and shake your right hand, too.)

280
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:14,955
(Do you know what that means?
I'll tell you.)

281
